  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7, boil a kettle, then take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Peel your <strong>potatoes</strong> and chop them into large bite-sized pieces, then add to a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook for 12-15 min or until fork-tender, then drain and return to the pot to steam dry</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1670929063437-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1670929063437-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1670929063437-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1670929063437-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1670929063437-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the potatoes are cooking, heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>sweetcorn</strong> (no need to drain) to the pan with a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 2-3 min or until slightly caramelised then reduce the heat to medium-high and cook for a further 1-2 min</p><p>Reboil half a kettle</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1670929068001-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1670929068001-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1670929068001-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1670929068001-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1670929068001-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the sweetcorn is caramelising, peel and finely dice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1670929085518-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1670929085518-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1670929085518-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1670929085518-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1670929085518-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once slightly caramelised, add the <strong>diced onion</strong> and <strong>chopped garlic</strong> to the pan and cook for 5-6 min or until slightly softened</p><p>Meanwhile, dissolve your <strong>chicken stock mix</strong> and <strong>Dijon mustard</strong> in 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[260ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[300ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> and 50ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[65ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [80ml]</span> <strong>milk </strong>– this is your <strong>chicken stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1670929095881-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1670929095881-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1670929095881-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1670929095881-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1670929095881-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has softened, add your <strong>diced chicken thigh</strong> to the pan with your <strong>dried thyme</strong> and a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until lightly browned</p><p>Once lightly browned, add 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp] </span><strong>flour</strong> to the pan and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Add the <strong>chicken stock</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat, once boiling reduce the heat to medium-high and cook for 4-5 min or until slightly thickened – this is your<strong> chicken & sweetcorn pie filling</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1670929106512-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1670929106512-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
